1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,002
[ Mouse squeaks ]

2
00:00:02,085 --> 00:00:04,171
[ Penguins chirp ]

3
00:00:05,297 --> 00:00:07,716
[ All cheering ]

4
00:00:09,635 --> 00:00:11,053
[ Screeches ]

5
00:00:12,971 --> 00:00:13,805
s Adventure time J

6
00:00:13,889 --> 00:00:15,015
J Come on, grab your friends &

7
00:00:15,057 --> 00:00:17,559
J We're going to
a very distant land 7

8
00:00:17,643 --> 00:00:20,521
s With Jake the dog
and Finn the human ;&

9
00:00:20,562 --> 00:00:22,105
s The fun will never end J

10
00:00:22,189 --> 00:00:24,483
J It's adventure time &

11
00:00:27,736 --> 00:00:31,448
[ Electronic hum ]

12
00:00:38,872 --> 00:00:40,499
Finn: Squish.

13
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:43,627
Photosynthesize!

14
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:46,338
Photosynthesize!

15
00:00:46,922 --> 00:00:49,216
Photo--
You grabbing a snack, Fern?

16
00:00:49,299 --> 00:00:50,050
Yeah.

17
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:53,053
Water and light combine
so I can make my own food.

18
00:00:53,387 --> 00:00:55,264
In case
I don't catch anything.

19
00:00:55,973 --> 00:00:57,599
Come on, man.
Don't be so dow --
[ Reel clicks, squeaks ]

20
00:00:57,683 --> 00:00:59,476
[ Gasps |
Hey, I got something!

21
00:00:59,935 --> 00:01:02,312
[ Reel clicking ]
Hey, I got something, too!

22
00:01:06,275 --> 00:01:07,317
Nice.

23
00:01:07,943 --> 00:01:09,403
[ Grunts ]

24
00:01:09,945 --> 00:01:11,071
[ Growling ]

25
00:01:11,154 --> 00:01:13,615
Oh, no!
Oh, no! Oh, no!

26
00:01:14,408 --> 00:01:16,201
[ Sighs ]

27
00:01:18,537 --> 00:01:20,122
Pretty weird fish, huh?

28
00:01:20,205 --> 00:01:23,500
That's me --
the dude who dinks it up,

29
00:01:23,584 --> 00:01:25,877
just like I dinked it up
when you left Ooo.

30
00:01:26,420 --> 00:01:28,088
I was supposed
to protect it.

31
00:01:28,255 --> 00:01:30,549
Instead,
it went all crazy.

32
00:01:30,674 --> 00:01:31,758
I didn't even help.

33
00:01:31,842 --> 00:01:33,844
I just covered myself
in root beer

34
00:01:33,885 --> 00:01:35,387
and danced around
like a dummy.

35
00:01:35,887 --> 00:01:39,600
I can't do anything right!

36
00:01:40,183 --> 00:01:41,893
Hey, stop it.

37
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:43,437
You need a squoze?

38
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:44,730
Yes.

39
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:47,274
[ Grunts ]

40
00:01:47,399 --> 00:01:48,734
I feel better.

41
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:51,570
Sometimes being a good dude
ain't about not dinking it.

42
00:01:51,903 --> 00:01:53,488
Learn from your dinks.

43
00:01:53,572 --> 00:01:56,074
Like, you know my first battle
with a giant?

44
00:01:56,158 --> 00:01:57,784
I never told anybody this,
but --

45
00:01:57,868 --> 00:01:59,369
You boom-boomed
in your shorts.

46
00:01:59,453 --> 00:02:01,496
I know.
I have your memories.

47
00:02:02,122 --> 00:02:04,124
Yeah, I boom-boomed.

48
00:02:04,207 --> 00:02:07,210
The point is I learned from it,
and now I'm Finn.

49
00:02:07,294 --> 00:02:09,504
You got to learn
how to be Fern.

50
00:02:09,588 --> 00:02:11,757
[ Stomping, rumbling ]

51
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,091
Both: What's that sound?

52
00:02:13,175 --> 00:02:14,718
Oh, I bet
it's @a monster.

53
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:16,928
Let's fight this dude
Fern's way.

54
00:02:17,012 --> 00:02:19,222
Yeah.
Fern's way.

55
00:02:19,306 --> 00:02:21,433
[ Stomping, rumbling continue ]

56
00:02:21,516 --> 00:02:23,143
Aaaaah!

57
00:02:23,185 --> 00:02:25,854
Both: Sweet P?
WEEEELL

58
00:02:25,896 --> 00:02:28,357
Both: Whoa!

59
00:02:28,523 --> 00:02:30,901
Sweet P:
Aaaaaaaaaaaah!
Both: [ Gasp ]

60
00:02:30,942 --> 00:02:36,031
Waaaaaaaaaaaaaah!

61
00:02:36,114 --> 00:02:38,909
Okay, Fern, what do you think
we should do next?

62
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:41,244
Mm, sever his tendons?

63
00:02:41,328 --> 00:02:42,037
[ Winces ]

64
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:45,957
Before you say no,
it would stop him from running.

65
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:48,627
We're gonna handle this
librarian style.

66
00:02:48,919 --> 00:02:50,003
[ Crying ]

67
00:02:50,087 --> 00:02:51,713
[ Whispering ] Shh.

68
00:02:51,797 --> 00:02:53,632
Librarian.
Kiss.

69
00:02:53,674 --> 00:02:58,095
You can renew the book
and bring it back next week.

70
00:02:58,178 --> 00:02:59,721
Library style.

71
00:02:59,805 --> 00:03:03,642
Squ-0-0-0ze.

72
00:03:03,684 --> 00:03:05,310
Ooh.

73
00:03:06,395 --> 00:03:08,980
Mm.
Great thinking, Fern.

74
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:12,067
I just copied you.
Is that thinking?

75
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:15,278
What up, buttercup?
Why you run, pork bun?

76
00:03:15,362 --> 00:03:17,155
The monster!

77
00:03:17,239 --> 00:03:19,116
Was it LSP?

78
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:23,954
The monster that whispers me
bad thoughts.

79
00:03:25,664 --> 00:03:30,168
[ Indistinct whispering ]

80
00:03:31,253 --> 00:03:32,003
[ Whispering stops ]

81
00:03:32,713 --> 00:03:35,549
Sweet P: Mommy and Daddy came
to save me,

82
00:03:35,632 --> 00:03:38,844
but they said
I was imagining things,

83
00:03:39,094 --> 00:03:41,430
which was true.

84
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:45,976
[ Indistinct whispering ]

85
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:49,855
Sweet P: But last night,
I really did see it.

86
00:03:51,773 --> 00:03:53,483
[ Screams ]

87
00:03:53,567 --> 00:03:56,528
And I've been running
and running since then.

88
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:58,321
Aww, Sweet P.

89
00:03:58,780 --> 00:04:01,324
It sounds like you might
just be having bad dreams.

90
00:04:01,408 --> 00:04:05,036
No, I only have
one dream anymore.

91
00:04:05,412 --> 00:04:08,039
[ Indistinct whispering ]

92
00:04:08,123 --> 00:04:10,834
Uhh...
Uhh...

93
00:04:11,084 --> 00:04:14,129
But the whisper monster is
even scarier,

94
00:04:14,212 --> 00:04:18,258
saying stuff like,
"Sweet P, you're bad.

95
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:21,511
You always have been bad."

96
00:04:21,595 --> 00:04:23,764
I don't want to be bad.

97
00:04:23,847 --> 00:04:25,390
[ Crying ]

98
00:04:25,474 --> 00:04:28,435
Oh, you're not bad.
You're super good.

99
00:04:28,643 --> 00:04:29,811
Now, let's get you home.

100
00:04:30,061 --> 00:04:31,271
But it's getting late,

101
00:04:31,313 --> 00:04:34,399
and bogs are super dangerous
to travel in at night.

102
00:04:34,483 --> 00:04:37,944
Your body will be preserved
for thousands of years.

103
00:04:38,028 --> 00:04:41,656
No one will ever find you.

104
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:44,284
[ Wailing ]
Fern!

105
00:04:44,993 --> 00:04:47,954
Okay, okay, we'll see you
in the morning, Tree Trunks.

106
00:04:48,747 --> 00:04:50,832
[ Telephone beeps ]
All right, bedtime,
Sweet P.

107
00:04:52,793 --> 00:04:55,003
You want me
to knock him out?

108
00:04:55,045 --> 00:04:58,548
Er, not this time.
How about a bedtime story?

109
00:04:58,632 --> 00:04:59,758
Yes, please.

110
00:04:59,841 --> 00:05:03,637
Once there was
a kingdom of spaghetti.

111
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:04,888
Mmm.

112
00:05:05,055 --> 00:05:06,640
[ Insects chirping ]

113
00:05:06,890 --> 00:05:09,434
[ Snoring ]

114
00:05:10,352 --> 00:05:12,187
[ Whispering ]
Punch, punch.

115
00:05:12,395 --> 00:05:13,688
Kiss, kiss.

116
00:05:13,772 --> 00:05:17,067
The Lich:
Listen to your bones.

117
00:05:19,069 --> 00:05:20,320
Fern.

118
00:05:20,403 --> 00:05:22,364
[ Teeth clicking ]

119
00:05:22,447 --> 00:05:23,448
Fern!

120
00:05:23,532 --> 00:05:24,449
[ Gasps |

121
00:05:25,450 --> 00:05:27,244
Hey. What's up?

122
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:28,578
I heard something.

123
00:05:28,662 --> 00:05:30,539
Can you see what it is
with your tree senses?

124
00:05:30,872 --> 00:05:32,541
I don't have those.
[ Rustle ]

125
00:05:38,672 --> 00:05:41,091
[ Footsteps ]

126
00:05:41,216 --> 00:05:43,343
Uh, can I help you?

127
00:05:43,385 --> 00:05:44,052
Oh, sorry.

128
00:05:44,094 --> 00:05:46,304
We heard you scuttling
around and thought --

129
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:46,972
What?

130
00:05:47,347 --> 00:05:49,349
You didn't hear me
"scuttling around."

131
00:05:49,432 --> 00:05:51,393
Foxes are silent hunters.

132
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:54,271
I mean, geez, do you know
how rude that is?

133
00:05:54,354 --> 00:05:56,982
[Groans] Gonna be brooding
about this all week.

134
00:05:57,065 --> 00:05:58,650
Sorry, man.

135
00:05:58,733 --> 00:05:59,901
[ Indistinct whispering ]
Look.

136
00:05:59,985 --> 00:06:01,653
[ Whispering continues ]

137
00:06:01,736 --> 00:06:03,822
Aah!
Get off him!

138
00:06:03,864 --> 00:06:04,906
Lich Hand: Huh?

139
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:06,783
Aah!
[ Grunts ]

140
00:06:10,662 --> 00:06:11,872
I got him!

141
00:06:12,539 --> 00:06:13,582
Oh, no.

142
00:06:13,665 --> 00:06:15,625
I know where I've seen
that thing before.

143
00:06:16,084 --> 00:06:21,172
[ Ominous tones play ]

144
00:06:25,385 --> 00:06:26,970
Huh?

145
00:06:27,053 --> 00:06:31,600
Lich Hand:
[ Laughs evilly ]

146
00:06:33,518 --> 00:06:35,395
BMO: Finn, Jake!
What's shaking?

147
00:06:35,437 --> 00:06:38,899
You will not believe
what just happened.

148
00:06:39,816 --> 00:06:43,194
It must've been the day that BMO
found that little sailor hat.

149
00:06:43,278 --> 00:06:44,112
Hold him down, Fern!

150
00:06:44,154 --> 00:06:46,990
That hand is
the flippin' Lich!

151
00:06:47,073 --> 00:06:47,908
I know.

152
00:06:47,991 --> 00:06:48,992
[ Chuckles evilly ]

153
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:52,829
Yes, child.
I returned once more to --

154
00:06:52,913 --> 00:06:54,623
Bah! Bah! Bah!
Bah! Evil!

155
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:57,500
You're gonna get it for messing
with our boy Sweet P.

156
00:06:57,584 --> 00:07:01,546
That vessel may appear harmless,
but he came from me.

157
00:07:01,630 --> 00:07:06,051
Once I remind him of his legacy,
The Lich shall reign once more.

158
00:07:06,134 --> 00:07:09,137
Isn't that right, son?
- Aah!

159
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:10,305
Finn!

160
00:07:10,388 --> 00:07:11,973
Lich Hand:
[ Laughs evilly ]

161
00:07:12,057 --> 00:07:14,684
Ugh!
I dinked it again!

162
00:07:14,726 --> 00:07:17,103
[ Grunts ]

163
00:07:17,187 --> 00:07:19,230
[ Panting ]

164
00:07:19,898 --> 00:07:22,567
Why did Mr. Hand
call me "son"?

165
00:07:22,651 --> 00:07:25,070
Was that my monster daddy?

166
00:07:25,153 --> 00:07:27,155
Okay, delegate,
delegate --

167
00:07:27,238 --> 00:07:28,949
Fern, stay here
and guard Sweet P.

168
00:07:29,032 --> 00:07:32,786
I'm gonna try and catch up.
Don't trust me
to guard anything.

169
00:07:32,869 --> 00:07:34,120
I'm a total scrub-up.

170
00:07:34,204 --> 00:07:37,040
Dude, there's already
one Lich loose in Ooo0.

171
00:07:37,123 --> 00:07:39,167
If Sweet Pea turns
e-v-i-l tonight,

172
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:40,502
there might be a second.

173
00:07:40,585 --> 00:07:42,253
I need you here.

174
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:43,922
You got this!

175
00:07:45,173 --> 00:07:46,257
You got this.

176
00:07:46,341 --> 00:07:48,593
[ The Lich's voice ]
Quickly, while the boy is gone,

177
00:07:48,677 --> 00:07:51,721
we must seek out
my well of power.

178
00:07:51,805 --> 00:07:52,764
Sweet P:
[ Normal voice ] No!

179
00:07:53,014 --> 00:07:55,725
Am I turning
into a monster?

180
00:07:55,976 --> 00:07:57,644
That's the working theory.

181
00:08:01,189 --> 00:08:02,857
Jake:I can't come
to the phone right now.

182
00:08:02,941 --> 00:08:05,944
I'm either hanging with Finn,
my kids, my G.F., or I'm dead.

183
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:06,987
Bye!
[Tone beeps]

184
00:08:07,070 --> 00:08:08,363
Hey, man,
hit me when you get this.

185
00:08:08,446 --> 00:08:11,741
[ Clicks tongue ]
Dude's missing a Lich fight.

186
00:08:11,783 --> 00:08:13,368
Okay, Lich.

187
00:08:13,451 --> 00:08:14,995
Get ready to die --
again --

188
00:08:15,078 --> 00:08:17,497
for, like,
the fifth time.

189
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:23,003
Oh, hey,
it's this awful place.

190
00:08:23,586 --> 00:08:26,214
[ Rustling ]

191
00:08:26,756 --> 00:08:28,591
Oh, you're tricky, huh?

192
00:08:37,726 --> 00:08:39,519
[ Indistinct whispering ]

193
00:08:40,395 --> 00:08:41,896
I can hear you down there!

194
00:08:42,022 --> 00:08:43,982
[ Whispering continues ]

195
00:08:44,024 --> 00:08:47,402
Speak up, man.
What?
[ Rustling ]

196
00:08:47,819 --> 00:08:51,031
Aah! Ooh!
Aaaaaah!

197
00:08:51,990 --> 00:08:53,324
The Lich:
[ Chuckles evilly ]

198
00:08:53,867 --> 00:08:56,411
You bested me
in many worlds, child,

199
00:08:56,494 --> 00:08:58,580
but I always return.

200
00:08:59,414 --> 00:09:00,707
[ Rock hisses ]
[ Grunts ]

201
00:09:01,624 --> 00:09:04,669
You're so evil, it's boring.
You're basic, man.

202
00:09:04,753 --> 00:09:05,837
Yes.

203
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:09,090
While a mortal world doubts
and questions,

204
00:09:09,174 --> 00:09:10,842
I know exactly what I am.

205
00:09:10,925 --> 00:09:12,969
I am the ceaseless wheel,

206
00:09:13,470 --> 00:09:15,805
the last scholar of Golb.

207
00:09:15,889 --> 00:09:18,058
I am your doom.

208
00:09:18,141 --> 00:09:20,310
Sweet P: Skull man!
Huh?

209
00:09:21,603 --> 00:09:23,938
I, too, am doom.

210
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:31,905
Hey, what's going on
up there?

211
00:09:31,988 --> 00:09:33,656
[ Laughs evilly ]

212
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:36,826
Child, you have failed.
The vessel has turned.

213
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:40,830
We reign now
as twin kings of ruin.

214
00:09:40,914 --> 00:09:42,415
Sweet P.

215
00:09:43,124 --> 00:09:45,627
I'm not a king of ruin.

216
00:09:46,169 --> 00:09:47,003
What?

217
00:09:47,170 --> 00:09:48,630
Iam sweet.

218
00:09:48,713 --> 00:09:50,924
You're just a naughty hand.

219
00:09:51,341 --> 00:09:52,967
Beast, obey me!

220
00:09:53,051 --> 00:09:54,552
Obey -- No!

221
00:09:54,636 --> 00:09:57,597
[ Grunting ]

222
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:59,390
[ Slice ]
Eesh.

223
00:09:59,516 --> 00:10:00,725
[ Groans ]

224
00:10:00,809 --> 00:10:03,353
[ Spirits groan, scream ]

225
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:05,355
Hooray!

226
00:10:05,522 --> 00:10:08,108
You're a natural!
But where's Fern?

227
00:10:08,191 --> 00:10:11,736
He wouldn't let me follow you,
so I knocked him out cold.

228
00:10:11,903 --> 00:10:14,322
Yeah, I met
my bio dad once, too.

229
00:10:14,405 --> 00:10:17,784
He wasn't evil incarnate, but
he was kind of a crummy dude.

230
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:21,037
T.T. and Mr. P. love you.
That's all that matters.

231
00:10:21,121 --> 00:10:23,790
Fern, Sweet P saved me
and slew The Lich!

232
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:26,000
That's great.

233
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:29,003
Sweet P:
You're just a naughty hand.

234
00:10:29,087 --> 00:10:31,381
The Lich:
Beast, obey me!

235
00:10:31,464 --> 00:10:32,257
Obey -- no!

236
00:10:32,841 --> 00:10:34,217
Male voice:
End of message.

237
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:36,553
To repeat this message,
press 7.

238
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:38,054
What?
- To save...

239
00:10:41,516 --> 00:10:43,101
Fern:I don't get it.

240
00:10:43,226 --> 00:10:45,603
Why isn't it working out
being myself?

241
00:10:45,687 --> 00:10:48,398
Finn's off having fun
defeating losers.

242
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:50,024
I can't even guard a baby.

243
00:10:50,692 --> 00:10:53,278
It doesn't matter
how hard I try.

244
00:10:53,361 --> 00:10:57,407
I'll always just be
in the shadow of the real Finn.

245
00:10:58,116 --> 00:11:01,744
Unless I could become...

246
00:11:01,828 --> 00:11:03,621
the only Finn.

247
00:11:03,705 --> 00:11:07,250
Uh, yeah, but that's
a weird thing to call me.

248
00:11:12,172 --> 00:11:15,884
J Come along with me J

249
00:11:15,967 --> 00:11:20,054
s And the butterflies and bees &

250
00:11:23,016 --> 00:11:25,268
This party is so crazy!

